<strong>1.3. COLLECTION OF AUTOMATIC INFORMATION/DETAILS/DATA, USE OF COOKIES AND OTHER TRACKING DEVICES</strong>

The Blackmelon and it’s third party service providers, which include advertisement on networks, use cookies, web beacons, and other tracking technologies to collect information/details/data about user’s use of the Blackmelon’s Website and/or app and Services, such as user’s browser type, ISP or operating system, domain name, access time, the URL of the previous website visited, page views, IP address, and the type of device that the user uses. The Blackmelon also track how frequently the user visits Website and/or app and use it’s services. The Blackmelon can use the information/details/data (including the information/details/data collected by the Blackmelon’s third party service providers) for Website and/or app  analytics (including to determine which portions of the Blackmelon’s Website and/or app  are used most frequently, what the Blackmelon’s users like/do not like), to assist the Blackmelon in determining relevant advertising (both on and off the Blackmelon’s  Website and/or app ), to evaluate the success of Blackmelon’s advertising campaigns, and as otherwise described in this policy. Currently, the Blackmelon do not honor browser requests not to be tracked.

The Blackmelon may obtain the user’s device ID, which is sent to Blackmelon's servers and used in fraud prevention efforts.

<strong>Cookies</strong>: The Blackmelon and its third party service providers collect information/details/data from the user by using cookies. A cookie is a small file stored on user's computer hard drive containing information/details/data about the user. The cookie helps the Blackmelon to analyze web traffic or informs the user about their use of a particular Website and/or app. Cookies allow web applications to respond to users an individual, tailoring its operations to the user’s needs, likes and dislikes by gathering and retaining information/details/data about user’s preferences. When visited the Website and/or app, Blackmelon may send one or more cookies (i.e., a small text file containing a string of alphanumeric characters) to user’s computer or smart phone that identifies user’s browser.

Some of these cookies may be connected to third-party companies or websites. The terms of use of such cookies are governed by this Policy and the privacy policy of the relevant third party Blackmelon or website. For example, Google measures the performance of advertisements by placing cookies on user’s computer when user clicks on advertisement. If user visit the Website when user have such cookies on user’s computer, Blackmelon and Google will be able to tell that the user saw the advertisement delivered by Google. The terms of use of these cookies are governed by this Policy and Google's Privacy Policy.

Disabling Cookies: user can choose to accept or decline cookies. Most web browsers automatically accept cookies, but user can usually modify own browser setting to decline cookies if user prefer. If user disable cookies user may be prevented from taking full advantage of the Website or the app because it may not function properly if the ability to accept cookies is disabled.

Clear GIFs, pixel tags and other technologies. Clear GIFs are tiny graphics with a unique identifier, similar in function to cookies. In contrast to cookies, which are stored on user’s computer's hard drive, clear GIFs are embedded invisibly on web pages. Blackmelon may use clear GIFs (a.k.a. web beacons, web bugs or pixel tags), in connection with Blackmelon’s Website to, among other things, track the activities of Website visitors, help us manage content, and compile statistics about Website usage. Blackmelon and its third party service providers also use clear GIFs in HTML emails to  Blackmelon’s customers, to help us track email response rates, identify when  Blackmelon’s emails are viewed, and track whether  Blackmelon’s emails are forwarded.
